func (r *SessionRepository) DeleteExpired() error
func (r *SessionRepository) DeleteByUserID(userID int64) error
```

### 3. `/Users/rollin/eaglepoint/w2t86/repo/internal/middleware/auth.go`
Fiber middleware. Cookie name: `session_token`.

```go
package middleware

// RequireAuth: reads session_token cookie, hashes it with SHA-256,
// looks up session in DB via SessionRepository, validates not expired,
// loads user, stores user in ctx.Locals("user").
// Returns 401 JSON {"error": "unauthorized"} if invalid.

// GetUser(c *fiber.Ctx) *models.User — helper to extract from Locals

type AuthMiddleware struct {
    sessionRepo *repository.SessionRepository
    userRepo    *repository.UserRepository
}
func NewAuthMiddleware(sr *repository.SessionRepository, ur *repository.UserRepository) *AuthMiddleware
func (m *AuthMiddleware) RequireAuth() fiber.Handler
```

### 4. `/Users/rollin/eaglepoint/w2t86/repo/internal/middleware/rbac.go`
```go
package middleware

// RequireRole(roles ...string) fiber.Handler
// Reads user from ctx.Locals("user"), checks role is in allowed list.
// Returns 403 JSON {"error": "forbidden"} if not.
// Must be used after RequireAuth.
func RequireRole(roles ...string) fiber.Handler
```

### 5. `/Users/rollin/eaglepoint/w2t86/repo/internal/middleware/ratelimit.go`
```go
package middleware

// In-memory sliding window rate limiter (per user ID key).
// CommentRateLimit(): 5 requests per 10 minutes per user_id (from Locals)
// Returns 429 JSON {"error": "rate limit exceeded"} if over limit.
// Use sync.Mutex + map[int64][]time.Time for the window.
type RateLimiter struct { mu sync.Mutex; windows map[string][]time.Time; limit int; window time.Duration }
func NewRateLimiter(limit int, window time.Duration) *RateLimiter
func (rl *RateLimiter) Middleware(keyFn func(*fiber.Ctx) string) fiber.Handler
```

### 6. `/Users/rollin/eaglepoint/w2t86/repo/internal/services/auth.go`
```go
package services

type AuthService struct {
    userRepo    *repository.UserRepository
    sessionRepo *repository.SessionRepository
    cfg         *config.Config
}

func NewAuthService(ur *repository.UserRepository, sr *repository.SessionRepository, cfg *config.Config) *AuthService

// Login: check user exists, not locked, password matches.
// On 5th failure: lock for 15 minutes, return error "account locked".
// On success: reset failed attempts, create session (24h), return raw token.
func (s *AuthService) Login(username, password string) (token string, user *models.User, err error)

// Logout: delete session by token hash
func (s *AuthService) Logout(token string) error

// Register: validate password >= 12 chars, hash, create user
func (s *AuthService) Register(username, email, password, role string) (*models.User, error)
```

Token generation: `crypto/rand` 32-byte → hex string. Store SHA-256 hash in DB.

### 7. `/Users/rollin/eaglepoint/w2t86/repo/internal/handlers/auth.go`
```go
package handlers

type AuthHandler struct { authService *services.AuthService }
func NewAuthHandler(as *services.AuthService) *AuthHandler

// GET  /login  — render login page (template "login")
// POST /login  — process login, set session_token cookie (HttpOnly, SameSite=Strict, Path=/), redirect to /dashboard
//               On error: re-render login with inline error message (HTMX-aware: check HX-Request header)
// POST /logout — clear cookie, delete session, redirect to /login
```

Use `c.Render()` for templates. For HTMX requests (HX-Request header = "true"), return just the form partial with error. For non-HTMX, return full page.

