## Files to Write

### 1. `/Users/rollin/eaglepoint/w2t86/repo/internal/repository/materials.go`
```go
package repository

type MaterialRepository struct { db *sql.DB }
func NewMaterialRepository(db *sql.DB) *MaterialRepository

// CRUD
func (r *MaterialRepository) Create(m *models.Material) (*models.Material, error)
func (r *MaterialRepository) GetByID(id int64) (*models.Material, error)
func (r *MaterialRepository) Update(id int64, fields map[string]interface{}) error
func (r *MaterialRepository) SoftDelete(id int64) error
func (r *MaterialRepository) List(limit, offset int, filters map[string]string) ([]models.Material, error)

// FTS5 search
func (r *MaterialRepository) Search(query string, limit, offset int) ([]models.Material, error)
// Uses: SELECT m.* FROM materials_fts fts JOIN materials m ON m.id = fts.rowid
//       WHERE materials_fts MATCH ? AND m.deleted_at IS NULL ORDER BY rank LIMIT ? OFFSET ?

// Inventory (used by order service)
func (r *MaterialRepository) Reserve(id int64, qty int) error   // available_qty -= qty, reserved_qty += qty; fail if available_qty < qty
func (r *MaterialRepository) Release(id int64, qty int) error   // available_qty += qty, reserved_qty -= qty
func (r *MaterialRepository) Fulfill(id int64, qty int) error   // reserved_qty -= qty (items actually issued)
```

### 2. `/Users/rollin/eaglepoint/w2t86/repo/internal/repository/engagement.go`
```go
package repository

type EngagementRepository struct { db *sql.DB }
func NewEngagementRepository(db *sql.DB) *EngagementRepository

// Browse history
func (r *EngagementRepository) RecordVisit(userID, materialID int64) error
func (r *EngagementRepository) GetHistory(userID int64, limit int) ([]models.BrowseHistory, error)

// Ratings
func (r *EngagementRepository) UpsertRating(materialID, userID int64, stars int) error
func (r *EngagementRepository) GetRating(materialID, userID int64) (*models.Rating, error)
func (r *EngagementRepository) GetAverageRating(materialID int64) (float64, int, error) // avg, count

// Comments
func (r *EngagementRepository) CreateComment(materialID, userID int64, body string, linkCount int) (*models.Comment, error)
func (r *EngagementRepository) GetComments(materialID int64, includeCollapsed bool, limit, offset int) ([]models.Comment, error)
func (r *EngagementRepository) ReportComment(commentID, reportedBy int64, reason string) error
// After insert into comment_reports: count unique reporters, if >= 3 set comments.status='collapsed'
func (r *EngagementRepository) CountRecentComments(userID int64, since time.Time) (int, error)

// Favorites
func (r *EngagementRepository) CreateList(userID int64, name, visibility string) (*models.FavoritesList, error)
func (r *EngagementRepository) GetLists(userID int64) ([]models.FavoritesList, error)
func (r *EngagementRepository) GetListByShareToken(token string) (*models.FavoritesList, error)
func (r *EngagementRepository) AddToList(listID, materialID int64) error
func (r *EngagementRepository) RemoveFromList(listID, materialID int64) error
func (r *EngagementRepository) GetListItems(listID int64) ([]models.FavoritesItem, error)
func (r *EngagementRepository) GenerateShareToken(listID int64, expiresAt time.Time) (string, error)
// Generate crypto/rand token, store in share_token + share_expires_at
func (r *EngagementRepository) UpdateListVisibility(listID int64, visibility string) error
```

### 3. `/Users/rollin/eaglepoint/w2t86/repo/internal/services/materials.go`
```go
package services

type MaterialService struct {
    materialRepo    *repository.MaterialRepository
    engagementRepo  *repository.EngagementRepository
    wordFilter      *WordFilter
}

func NewMaterialService(mr *repository.MaterialRepository, er *repository.EngagementRepository) *MaterialService

func (s *MaterialService) Search(query string, filters map[string]string, limit, offset int) ([]models.Material, error)
func (s *MaterialService) GetByID(id int64) (*models.Material, error)
func (s *MaterialService) Create(m *models.Material, actorID int64, db *sql.DB) (*models.Material, error) // writes material_versions
func (s *MaterialService) Update(id int64, fields map[string]interface{}, actorID int64, db *sql.DB) error // writes material_versions

// Comments: validate body <= 500 chars, count links (href= occurrences) <= 2
// Check sensitive word filter, check rate limit via engagementRepo.CountRecentComments
func (s *MaterialService) AddComment(materialID, userID int64, body string) (*models.Comment, error)

// Ratings: one per student
func (s *MaterialService) Rate(materialID, userID int64, stars int) error

// Favorites
func (s *MaterialService) CreateFavoritesList(userID int64, name, visibility string) (*models.FavoritesList, error)
func (s *MaterialService) AddToFavorites(listID, materialID, userID int64) error
func (s *MaterialService) GetShareLink(listID int64, userID int64) (string, error)
// Generates share token with 7-day expiry
```

Also implement `WordFilter` in this file:
```go
type WordFilter struct { patterns []*regexp.Regexp }
func NewWordFilter(words []string) *WordFilter
func (wf *WordFilter) Contains(text string) (bool, string) // returns true + matched word
```

### 4. `/Users/rollin/eaglepoint/w2t86/repo/internal/handlers/materials.go`
```go
package handlers

type MaterialHandler struct {
    materialService *services.MaterialService
    authMiddleware  *middleware.AuthMiddleware
}
func NewMaterialHandler(ms *services.MaterialService) *MaterialHandler

// Routes:
// GET  /materials          — search page (render "materials/list")
// GET  /materials/search   — HTMX search partial (hx-get with ?q=&subject=&grade=), renders "partials/material_cards"
// GET  /materials/:id      — material detail page (render "materials/detail"), records browse history
// POST /materials/:id/rate — rate material (HTMX, returns updated star widget partial)
// POST /materials/:id/comments — add comment (HTMX, returns updated comments partial or error)
// POST /comments/:id/report   — report comment (HTMX, returns updated comment partial)

// Admin routes:
// GET  /admin/materials/new — new material form
// POST /admin/materials     — create material
// GET  /admin/materials/:id/edit — edit form
// PUT  /admin/materials/:id  — update material
// DELETE /admin/materials/:id — soft delete

// Favorites routes:
// GET  /favorites           — list user's favorites lists
// POST /favorites           — create new list
// POST /favorites/:id/items — add material to list
// DELETE /favorites/:id/items/:materialID — remove
// GET  /favorites/:id/share — generate/show share link
// GET  /share/:token        — public shared list (no auth required, check expiry)
```

All endpoints that mutate state should be HTMX-aware (check HX-Request header). Return partials for HTMX, full pages otherwise.

### 5. Templates to create:

**`/Users/rollin/eaglepoint/w2t86/repo/web/templates/materials/list.html`**
- Extends base layout
- Search bar: `hx-get="/materials/search"` `hx-trigger="keyup delay:300ms"` `hx-target="#material-results"` `hx-include="[name='q'],[name='subject'],[name='grade']"`
- Subject/grade filter dropdowns (same hx-include)
- Results div `id="material-results"` with hx-indicator
- Empty state message

**`/Users/rollin/eaglepoint/w2t86/repo/web/templates/partials/material_cards.html`**
- Grid of material cards (title, author, subject, availability badge, avg stars)
- Empty state if no results

**`/Users/rollin/eaglepoint/w2t86/repo/web/templates/materials/detail.html`**
- Material title, author, publisher, edition, subject, grade
- Availability badge
- Star rating widget (1-5 radio buttons, hx-post on change, shows avg + count)
- Comments section with add-comment form
- Each comment: username, date, body, report button
- Collapsed comments show "Content hidden - pending review" with toggle

**`/Users/rollin/eaglepoint/w2t86/repo/web/templates/partials/comment_form.html`**
- Textarea (max 500 chars, char counter), submit button, error message

**`/Users/rollin/eaglepoint/w2t86/repo/web/templates/favorites/list.html`**
- User's favorites lists (name, visibility badge, item count)
- Create new list form (inline, HTMX)
- Share link button (copies to clipboard or shows link)

Write complete, compilable Go code. All handlers must have the correct template rendering calls. Templates must use valid Go html/template syntax. Import paths must use module `w2t86`."}

