//
// Two detection strategies are applied independently:
//
//  1. Exact identifier match — same email address (the unique external identifier
//     in this system). Score = 1.0. Email is the closest analogue to a stable
//     government or student ID in the schema; any two accounts sharing the same
//     email are definitively the same person.
//
//  2. Fuzzy identity match — composite weighted score:
//
//       score = 0.6 × username_similarity  +  0.4 × dob_match
//
//     where username_similarity is the Levenshtein-based 0–1 similarity between
//     (lowercased) usernames (used as a name proxy when no dedicated name column
//     exists) and dob_match is 1.0 if both records have identical, non-null
//     date_of_birth values, 0.0 otherwise.
//
//     A pair is included when the combined score ≥ 0.65.  This threshold
//     ensures that neither signal alone is sufficient:
//       - DOB match only (0.4) → below threshold, excluded.
//       - Username similarity only (max 0.6) → at threshold only for identical
//         usernames; anything less is excluded unless DOB also matches.
//       - Both signals combined → reliably flag probable duplicates.
